to the editor the president 's address to congress and the country included as expected a statement of the need for a strong military to keep the peace it also included a pledge to work with our allies and friends to be a force for good and a champion of freedom in promoting a distinctly american internationalism transcript feb 28 all well and good but regrettably there was no reference to another essential element in that effort america 's diplomatic arm surely the country 's first line of defense where that falls short and today our diplomatic service is both seriously underfinanced and in need of reform achieving our interests abroad is not furthered congress and the country should hear that from the country 's no 1 diplomat the president bruce laingen washington march 1 2001 the writer is president of the american academy of diplomacy

